comment: Parker (SAS) extends his arms into Walker (CHA) and pushes off to create space away from the ball.
Parker (SAS) moves his pivot foot while under the rim.
Green (SAS) maintains legal guarding position, retreating along Lin's (CHA) path, then gets both hands on the ball forcing a jump ball.
Lin (CHA) makes contact with Green's (SAS) arm that affects his ability to tap the jump ball.
Duncan (SAS) extends his leg into Walker's (CHA) path, without giving him room to avoid the contact and contact occurs to Duncan's leg.
LHH shows Leonard (SAS) makes contact with Lin (CHA) that affects his RSBQ.

[Observable in production angle] Leonard (SAS) appears to maintain a legal guarding position on Lin (CHA). There is no angle that conclusively shows he places two hands on him above the free-throw line extended (which is illegal).
Batum (CHA) legally contests Leonard (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Batum (CHA) legally contests Leonard (SAS) jump shot attempt, giving him room to land. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Parker (SAS) makes contact with Lin (CHA) that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Duncan (SAS) firms up as he sets the screen on Walker (CHA) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The two players make incidental contact that causes Duncan to lose his balance.
[Incidental or immaterial] Zeller (CHA) briefly grabs Aldridge's (SAS) jersey on the rebound, but it does not affect Aldridge's ability to get the rebound.
Lin (CHA) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Green's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that possession be awarded to SAS was upheld.
